%N A389790 Number of ways to write 2*n as p + p' + q + q', where p and q are primes with p <= q, and r' is the first prime greater than r.
%C A389790 Conjecture: a(n) > 0 for all n >= 474.
%C A389790 This is an analog of Goldbach's conjecture. It has been verified for n <= 2*10^5.
